<br>
1. Read the EQ manual for the most basic commands. You don't have to know or read it entirely. Just enough for you to move about and be able to target and kill things effectively and be able to survive your inital encounters. The advanced commands you can learn later. <br>
<br>
2. Read the fantastic EQ web sites. <br>
<br>
You want directions? Then go bookmark the EQAtlas web site. It has detailed maps of every region in Norrath. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqatlas.com">www.eqatlas.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
You need info on spells? You want a list of spells for your spellcaster? Want to know where to locate particular spells? Simply visit EQ Casters Realm web site and it's already listed for you. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com">eq.castersrealm.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Need more info on quests? Or monsters? Or info on magic items? Allakhazam does it best. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.allakhazam.com">www.allakhazam.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <br>
<br>
I'm not suggesting newbies to read everything. That's impossible. But I am suggesting they read a little before playing. In particular, read the topics and sections regarding your character's chosen class and race.... and you will be up and running in no time. Cheers. <br>
